Class Vehicle

java.lang.Object
pt.ipp.isep.dei.g312.domain.Vehicle
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Vehicle>
public class Vehicle extends Object implements Comparable<Vehicle>
Represents a vehicle with attributes to manage registration, brand, model, type, weight parameters, kilometers, and check-up details.

      public void registerCheckUp(double kmAtLastCheckUp, Date checkUpDate)
      Register a new check-up for the vehicle with the typed kilometers and date.
      Parameters:

      checkUpDate - The date when the last check-up was done.

    • isCheckUpDue

      public boolean isCheckUpDue()
      Boolean method to determines if the vehicle is due for a check-up or not, based on the check-up frequency and its current kilometers. A check-up is considered due if the current kilometers are within 5% of the kilometers calculated for the next check-up or if the current kilometers have exceeded the calculated kilometers for the next check-up.
      Returns:
      true if the vehicle needs a check-up, false if it doens't need a check-up.
